message.content:
cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

The paper discusses a model for visual perception, specifically illusory contrast perception induced by surrounding orientations. It draws inspiration from the primary visual cortex V1 and uses numerical tests to validate the model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses efficient representation properties, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) and the use of numerical tests, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
